# V2 Apply Checklist

Read when: applying/migrating templates into a project.
Skip when: templates are already applied and validated.

## 1) Apply Files (Only)
- [ ] `AI_AGENT.md.template` copied to `AI_AGENT.md`
- [ ] `AI_MEMORY.md.template` copied to `docs/AI_MEMORY.md`
- [ ] `MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md.template` copied to `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` (Tier B/C required; Tier A optional)
- [ ] `PROJECT_CANVAS.md.template` copied to `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md`
- [ ] `TECH_STACK.md.template` copied to `docs/TECH_STACK.md`
- [ ] `ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md.template` copied to `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md`
- [ ] `OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md.template` copied to `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md`
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md.template` copied to `CHANGELOG.md`
- [ ] `QUICKSTART_5_MIN.md.template` copied to `docs/QUICKSTART_5_MIN.md`
- [ ] `PLACEHOLDER_REFERENCE.md.template` copied to `docs/PLACEHOLDER_REFERENCE.md`
- [ ] `UPGRADE_GUIDE.md.template` copied to `docs/UPGRADE_GUIDE.md`
- [ ] `ci.yml.template` copied to `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
- [ ] `TEMPLATE_INDEX.yaml.template` copied to `docs/TEMPLATE_INDEX.yaml`
- [ ] `scripts/check_template_drift.sh.template` copied to `scripts/check_template_drift.sh`
- [ ] `scripts/placeholder_allowlist.txt.template` copied to `scripts/placeholder_allowlist.txt` (optional but recommended)
- [ ] Optional add-ons copied only if needed
	- `addons/README.md.template`
	- `addons/.gitignore.template`
	- `addons/CONTRIBUTING.md.template`
	- `addons/LICENSE.template`
	- `addons/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md.template`
	- `addons/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.md.template`
	- `addons/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.md.template`
	- `addons/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml.template`
	- `addons/docker-compose.local.yml.template`
	- `addons/MULTI_APP_SERVER_BLUEPRINT.md.template`
	- `addons/FIRST_SESSION_PROMPT.txt.template`
	- `addons/ADR_TEMPLATE.md.template`
	- `addons/ADVANCED_VERIFICATION_PLAYBOOK.md.template`
	- `addons/AI_OPERATING_CONTRACT.md.template` (legacy compatibility only)

## 2) Run Manual Validation
- [ ] Complete `TEMPLATE_VALIDATION_CHECKLIST.md`

## 3) Run Automated Validation
- [ ] Run `scripts/validate_templates.sh` (if included)
- [ ] Optional: use `scripts/bootstrap_agent_ready.sh` for one-command apply + placeholder fill + validation + readiness report
- [ ] For large-scale standardization, choose `--tier-profile auto|A|B|C` explicitly during bootstrap
- [ ] Run `scripts/check_template_drift.sh . /path/to/templates-v2` to confirm applied version parity
- [ ] For version bumps, follow `docs/UPGRADE_GUIDE.md`

## 4) Canonical Startup + Final Baseline
- [ ] Human startup instruction points to `AI_AGENT.md`
- [ ] If `AI_OPERATING_CONTRACT.md` is used, it mirrors `AI_AGENT.md` (no separate rules)
- [ ] `AI_CONTEXT.md` generation command defined
- [ ] Verify gate command defined
- [ ] Changelog contains `Unreleased`
